{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c6d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290g–1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"290g–1"},"text":"§ 290g–1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appointment of Governor and Alternate Governor; rank, duties, and compensation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c6e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290g–1/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The President shall appoint a Governor, and an Alternate Governor, of the Fund—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c6f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290g–1/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by and with the advice and consent of the Senate; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c70-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290g–1/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" from among individuals serving as officials required by law to be appointed by and with the advice and consent of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c71-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290g–1/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Governor, or in his absence the Alternate Governor, on the instructions of the President, shall cast the votes of the United States for the Director to represent the United States in the Fund. The Director representing the United States and his Alternate, if they are citizens of the United States, may, in the discretion of the President, receive such compensation, allowances, and other benefits not exceeding those authorized for a chief of mission under the Foreign Service Act of 1980 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s3901"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 3901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8ede2c72-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/302/tII/s203"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–302, title II, § 203","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-05-31"},"text":"May 31, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/593"},"text":"90 Stat. 593","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465/tII/s2206/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465, title II, § 2206(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2161"},"text":"94 Stat. 2161","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166/s2/bb"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166, § 2(bb)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1290"},"text":"126 Stat. 1290","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8ede2c73-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8ede2c74-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8ede2c75-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Foreign Service Act of 1980, referred to in subsec. (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2071"},"text":"94 Stat. 2071","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 52 (§ 3901 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s3901"},"text":"section 3901 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8ede2c76-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (a) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (a) read as follows: “The President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, shall appoint a Governor, and an Alternate Governor, of the Fund.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465","children":[],"tail":" substituted “a chief of mission under the Foreign Service Act of 1980” for “a Chief of Mission, class 2, within the meaning of the Foreign Service Act of 1946, as amended”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8ede2c77-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id8ede2c78-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2012 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166","children":[],"tail":" effective 60 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2012","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to appointments made on and after that effective date, including any nomination pending in the Senate on that date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166/s6/a"},"text":"section 6(a) of Pub. L. 112–166","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s113"},"text":"section 113 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id8ede2c79-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-02-15"},"text":"Feb. 15, 1981","children":[],"tail":", except as otherwise provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465/s2403"},"text":"section 2403 of Pub. L. 96–465","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s3901"},"text":"section 3901 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
